        <usage>&lt;DIV STYLE="text-align:Left;"&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Removes regional trends by fitting polynomial surfaces to the data. The residual (original minus trend) highlights local anomalies.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;1st Order: Fits and removes a plane (linear gradient removal)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;2nd Order: Fits and removes a quadratic surface (curved trend removal)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;More geologically meaningful than frequency domain regional removal.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</usage>
